ience in Islamic philosophy\n|publisher=[[Routledge Encyclopedia of Philosophy]]\n|accessdate=3 February 2008\n}}\n\n* {{citation\n|date=2008\n|volume=1\n|page=1667\n|chapter=M\n|publisher=Springer\n|editor-last=Selin\n|editor-first=Helaine\n|isbn=9781402045592\n|encyclopedia=Encyclopaedia of the History of Science, Technology, and Medicine in Non-Western Cultures\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n|last=Van Sertima\n|first=Ivan\n|title=Golden Age of the Moor\n|date=1992\n|url={{google books|plainurl=yes|id=1F9HPuDkySsC|p=382}}\n|author-link=Ivan Van Sertima\n|publisher=[[Transaction Publishers]]\n|isbn=1-56000-581-5\n|oclc=123168739}}\n\n* {{Citation\n|title=Alhacen's theory of visual perception: a critical edition, with English translation and commentary, of the first three books of Alhacen's De aspectibus, the medieval Latin version of Ibn al-Haytham's Kitab al-Manazir\n|date=2001\n|series=Transactions of the American Philosophical Society\n|volume=91-4, 91\u20135\n|location=Philadelphia\n|publisher=[[American Philosophical Society]] & DIANE Publishing\n|editor-last=Smith|editor-first=A. Mark\n|isbn=978-0-87169-914-5\n|oclc=163278528\n|translator-last=Smith|translator-first=A. Mark\n}} ([https://www.jstor.org/stable/3657358 Books I-III (2001) Vol 1 Commentary and Latin text via JSTOR]; [https://www.jstor.org/stable/3657357?seq=1#page_thumbnails_tab_contents Vol 2 English translation I:TOCp339-341, II:TOCp415-6, III:TOCp559-560, Notes 681ff, Bibl. via JSTOR])\n\n* {{Citation\n|last=Smith\n|first=A. Mark\n|title=What is the History of Medieval Optics Really About?\n|date=June 2004\n|url=http://www.amphilsoc.org/sites/default/files/480202.pdf\n|journal=Proceedings of the American Philosophical Society\n|volume=148\n|issue=2\n|pages=180\u2013194\n|jstor=1558283\n|url-status=dead\n|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111018045417/http://www.amphilsoc.org/sites/default/files/480202.pdf\n|archive-date=18 October 2011\n|df=\n|pmid=15338543\n}}\n* {{Citation\n|last=Smith\n|first=