ytham sur la vision binoculaire: un pr\u00e9curseur de l'optique physiologique\n|date=2003\n|journal=Arabic Sciences and Philosophy\n|volume=13|issue=1|pages=79\u201399\n|publisher=Cambridge University Press\n|doi=10.1017/S0957423903003047\n}}\n\n*{{citation\n|last=Rooney\n|first=Anne\n|title=The History of Physics\n|date=2012\n|chapter=Ibn Al-Haytham\n|publisher=The Rosen Publishing Group\n|isbn=9781448873715\n}}\n\n* {{citation\n|last=Rosenthal\n|first=Franz\n|title=Al-Mubashshir ibn F\u00e2tik. Prolegomena to an Abortive Edition\n|date=1960\u20131961\n|author-link=Franz Rosenthal\n|journal=Oriens\n|volume=13/14\n|pages=132\u2013158, 136\u20137\n|publisher=[[Brill Publishers]]\n|doi=10.2307/1580309\n|jstor=1580309\n}}\n\n* {{citation\n|title=Cleomedes c. 1st century AD) on the celestial illusion, atmospheric enlargement and size-distance invariance\n|date=2000\n|last1=Ross|first1=H.E.\n|journal=Perception\n|volume=29\n|issue=7\n|pages=853\u2013861\n|doi=10.1068/p2937\n|pmid=11064807\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n|title=The mystery of the moon illusion: Exploring size perception\n|year=2002\n|last1=Ross\n|last2=Plug\n|first1=H .E.\n|first2=C.\n|publisher=Oxford University Press\n|isbn=9780198508625\n|bibcode=2002mmi..book.....R\n}}\n\n* {{citation\n|title=Did Ptolemy understand the moon illusion?\n|date=1976\n|last1=Ross\n|last2=Ross\n|first1=H .E.\n|first2=G .M.\n|journal=Perception\n|volume=5\n|issue=4\n|pages=377\u2013385\n|doi=10.1068/p050377\n|pmid=794813\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n|last=Rottman\n|first=J.|title=A first course in Abstract Algebra\n|date=28 February 2000\n|publisher=Prentice Hall\n|isbn=0-13-011584-3\n|oclc=42960682\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n|last=Rozenfeld|first=Boris A.\n|title=A History of Non-Euclidean Geometry: Evolution of the Concept of a Geometric Space\n|date=1988\n|publisher=[[Springer Science+Business Media]]\n|isbn=0-387-96458-4\n|oclc=15550634\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n|title=Encyclopedia of the History of Arabic Science\n|date=1996\n|last1=Rozenfeld\n|las